# Architecture — Clean Architecture, Feature-First

```
lib/
├── main.dart / app.dart / initialization.dart
├── core/            # DI, config, database (drift), network, routing, state, theme, widgets
├── services/        # cross-cutting app services (downloads, live activity, updates, …)
└── features/<feature>/                       # scaffold via `mason make feature`
    ├── data/
    │   ├── data_sources/   <f>_local_datasource.dart + <f>_remote_datasource.dart
    │   └── repositories/   <f>_repository_imp.dart  @Injectable(as: <F>Repository)
    ├── domain/
    │   ├── entities/       <f>_entity.dart          (plain models)
    │   └── repositories/   <f>_repository.dart      (abstract interface)
    └── presentation/
        ├── pages/          <f>_page.dart            @RoutePage wrapper
        │   └── mobile/     <f>_page_mobile.dart     the screen tree
        ├── state/bloc/     <f>_bloc.dart, _event.dart, _state.dart
        └── widgets/        feature widget classes
```

Shared UI/utilities live in `lib/core/`, imported via
`package:hondana/core/core.dart`. No `packages/` monorepo, no Firebase.

## Mandatory feature structure

Generate features with `mason make feature --feature_name <name> -o lib/features`
(brick in `bricks/feature/`) — never hand-roll folders. Rules:

- `pages/` holds **two things**: the thin `@RoutePage` wrapper (`<f>_page.dart` —
  provides the Bloc, returns `PageLayoutBuilder(mobile: …)`) and the mobile
  implementation (`mobile/<f>_page_mobile.dart` — the real `AppScaffold` tree).
- The repository **interface** is in `domain/repositories/`; its
  `@Injectable(as: …)` **implementation** and the `@injectable` local/remote
  **data sources** are in `data/`.
- Domain models are `*_entity.dart` under `domain/entities/` (no drift/DTO types).
- Mirror the `auth` feature in the sibling `shadows` project exactly.

## Layer boundaries

- **Pages hold no business logic.** They compose a Bloc + UI. Orchestration
  (downloads, app-lock, library updates, source resolution) lives in
  `data/`/`domain/` services and is driven through the Bloc.
- **No network or database access in presentation.** Sources/repositories fetch
  and expose `Stream`s / result types; Blocs call them; pages render state.
- **Keep drift types out of `domain/`.** Map rows to domain entities at the data
  boundary (`Manga.fromData(...)`).
- **Repositories** expose intent-level methods and `Stream`s; concrete sources /
  drift live behind them.

## Features

`browse` (sources / extensions / global search), `library`, `manga` (details),
`reader`, `downloads`, `history`, `updates`, `more` (settings), `main` (shell).

## Sources & extensions

Mihon's source system is ported under `features/browse/`: `domain/source/`
(the `Source` abstraction + `SManga`/`SChapter`/`MangasPage`/`Filter` models),
`data/source/` (`HttpSource` base, `LocalSource`, and site families). Resolve by
id via `SourceManager`.
